TCL Dictionary
    A dictionary is an arrangement for mapping values to keys.
    In Tcl, a dictionary is a data structure that associates keys with values. 
    It is similar to an array, but unlike an array, the keys can be any Tcl value, not just integers or strings.
syntax:
      dict set dictname key value
              ( or ) 
      dict create dictname key1 value1 key2 value2 .. keyn valuen
Examples :
        dict set colours colour1 red 
        puts $colours
        dict set colours colour2 green
        puts $colours
        set colour [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white" colour3 "blue"]
        puts $colour
Build the functionality in dict:
      1. Size of dict
      2. Dictionary iteration
      3. Value for key in dict
      4. All keys in dict
      5. All values in dict
      6. keys exist in dict
      
1. size of dict:
syntax:
      [dict size dictname]
Example:
      set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
      puts [dict size $colours]

2. Dictionary Iteration:
    A simple dictionary iteration for printing keys and valued of the dictionary.
Example:
      set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
      foreach item [dict keys $colours] {
       set value [dict get $colours $item]
       puts $value
      }
      
3. Value for key in dict:
syntax:
      [dict get $dictname $keyname]
Example:
        set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
        set value [dict get $colours colour1]
        puts $value
        
4.  All keys in dict:
syntax:
        [dict keys $dictname]
Example :
        set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
        set keys [dict keys $colours]
        puts $keys

5. All Values in dict
syntax:
        [dict values $dictname]
Example :
        set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
        set values [dict values $colours]
        puts $values

6. Key Exists in dict:
syntax:
      [dict values $dictname]
Example:
        set colours [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white"]
        set result [dict exists $colours colour1]
        puts $result
        
7. set the values in dict:
Example:
        set colour [dict create colour1 "black" colour2 "white" colour3 "blue"]
        puts $colour
        dict set colour colour4 "orange"
        puts $colour
8. remove a key-value pair from the dict:
Example:
      set colour [dict create colour1 {"black" "purpple" } colour2 "white" colour3 "blue" colour4 "orange"]
      puts $colour
      dict unset colour colour1
      puts $colour



